ions%20on%20unnatural%20sex%20and%20adultery%20that%20were%20diluted%20and%20struck%20down%20respectively%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20IPC%2C%20Section%20377%20says%20%26quot%3Bwhoever%20voluntarily%20has%20carnal%20intercourse%20against%20the%20order%20of%20nature%20with%20any%20man%2C%20woman%20or%20animal%2C%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20%5Bimprisonment%20for%20life%5D%2C%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20either%20description%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20ten%20years%2C%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%206%2C%202018%2C%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20unanimously%20decriminalised%20a%20part%20of%20Section%20377.%20However%2C%20the%20provision%20still%20stood%20in%20the%20statute%20book%20to%20deal%20with%20unnatural%20sexual%20offences%20against%20minors%2C%20against%20their%20consent%20and%20bestiality.%20In%20the%20new%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20there%20is%20no%20provision%20on%20%26quot%3Bunnatural%20sex%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2027%2C%202018%2C%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20unanimously%20struck%20off%20from%20the%20statute%20books%20Section%20497%20of%20IPC%20which%20made%20adultery%20a%20criminal%20offence%20for%20men%20but%20did%20not%20penalise%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Section%20497%2C%20%26quot%3BWhoever%20has%20sexual%20intercourse%20with%20a%20person%20who%20is%20and%20whom%20he%20knows%20or%20has%20reason%20to%20believe%20to%20be%20the%20wife%20of%20another%20man%2C%20without%20the%20consent%20or%20connivance%20of%20that%20man%2C%20such%20sexual%20intercourse%20not%20amounting%20to%20the%20offence%20of%20rape%2C%20is%20guilty%20of%20the%20offence%20of%20adultery%2C%20and%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20either%20description%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20five%20years%2C%20or%20with%20fine%2C%20or%20with%20both.%20In%20such%20case%20the%20wife%20shall%20not%20be%20punishable%20as%20an%20abettor%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20said%20that%20acts%20of%20adultery%20will%20not%20qualify%20as%20a%20crime%2C%20although%20they%20would%20still%20be%20grounds%20for%20civil%20action%20and%20divorce.%20Under%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20there%20is%20no%20provision%20related%20to%20the%20offence%20of%20adultery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20was%20a%20punishable%20offence%20under%20Section%20309%20of%20the%20IPC%20until%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20Mental%20Healthcare%20Act%20in%202017%2C%20which%20in%20effect%20decriminalised%20suicide%20by%20creating%20a%20massive%20exception%20to%20Section%20309.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20section%20115%20of%20the%20Mental%20Healthcare%20Act%20of%202017%2C%20there%20was%20a%20presumption%20of%20severe%20stress%20in%20case%20of%20an%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20notwithstanding%20anything%20contained%20in%20section%20309%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20any%20person%20who%20attempts%20to%20commit%20suicide%20shall%20be%20presumed%2C%20unless%20proved%20otherwise%2C%20to%20have%20severe%20stress%20and%20shall%20not%20be%20tried%20and%20punished%20under%20the%20said%20Code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20said%20the%20appropriate%20government%20shall%20have%20a%20duty%20to%20provide%20care%2C%20treatment%20and%20rehabilitation%20to%20a%20person%2C%20having%20severe%20stress%20and%20who%20attempted%20to%20commit%20suicide%2C%20to%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20recurrence%20of%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20there%20is%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20separate%20offence%20of%20an%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20as%20in%20section%20309%20of%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20bill%20does%20have%20Section%20224%20which%20criminalises%20an%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20to%20compel%20or%20restrain%20exercise%20of%20lawful%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Section%20224%20of%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20%26quot%3BWhoever%20attempts%20to%20commit%20suicide%20with%20the%20intent%20to%20compel%20or%20restrain%20any%20public%20servant%20from%20discharging%20his%20official%20duty%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20simple%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20one%20year%20or%20with%20fine%20or%20with%20both%20or%20with%20community%20service.%26quot%3B%20There%20are%20similar%20other%20various%20provisions%20related%20to%20defamation%20and%20offence%20against%20women%2C%20which%20are%20being%20sought%20to%20be%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20highlights%20of%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%202023%20is%20that%20it%20seeks%20to%20repeal%20the%20offence%20of%20sedition%20under%20the%20IPC%20and%20provides%20capital%20sentence%20as%20the%20maximum%20punishment%20for%20crimes%20such%20as%20mob%20lynching%20and%20rape%20of%20minors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20IPC%20has%20511%20sections%2C%20the%20BNS%20Bill%20contains%20356%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20IPC%2C%20Section%20124-A%20deals%20with%20offence%20of%20sedition%20and%20prescribes%20a%20sentence%20of%20life%20imprisonment%20or%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20three%20years%2C%20to%20which%20a%20fine%20may%20be%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20provision%20150%20under%20the%20chapter%20pertaining%20to%20offences%20against%20the%20State%20talks%20about%20acts%20endangering%20the%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhoever%2C%20purposely%20or%20knowingly%2C%20by%20words%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20or%20by%20signs%2C%20or%20by%20visible%20representation%2C%20or%20by%20electronic%20communication%20or%20by%20use%20of%20financial%20mean%2C%20or%20otherwise%2C%20excites%20or%20attempts%20to%20excite%2C%20secession%20or%20armed%20rebellion%20or%20subversive%20activities%2C%20or%20encourages%20feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%20or%20endangers%20sovereignty%20or%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%3B%20%26quot%3Bor%20indulges%20in%20or%20commits%20any%20such%20act%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20seven%20years%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20section%20150%20of%20the%20BNS%20Bill%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20punishment%20for%20the%20offence%20of%20murder%20is%20covered%20under%20Section%20302%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20it%20has%20been%20covered%20under%20Provision%20101%20of%20the%20BNS%20Bill.%20The%20punishment%20for%20murder%2C%20that%20is%20life%20term%20or%20death%20sentence%2C%20remains%20unchanged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20bill%20proposes%20to%20make%20mob%20lynching%20a%20separate%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20provision%20101%20(2)%20of%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20group%20of%20five%20or%20more%20persons%20acting%20in%20concert%20commits%20murder%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20race%2C%20caste%20or%20community%2C%20sex%2C%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20language%2C%20personal%20belief%20or%20any%20other%20ground%20each%20member%20of%20such%20group%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20death%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20term%20which%20shall%20not%20be%20less%20than%20seven%20years%2C%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine.%26quot%3B%20Similarly%2C%20the%20BNS%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20make%20a%20new%20provision%20on%20%26quot%3Bsnatching%26quot%3B%20under%20Section%20302%20which%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BTheft%20is%20'snatching'%20if%2C%20in%20order%20to%20commit%20theft%2C%20the%20offender%20suddenly%20or%20quickly%20or%20forcibly%20seizes%20or%20secures%20or%20grabs%20or%20takes%20away%20from%20any%20person%20or%20from%20his%20possession%20any%20moveable%20property.%26quot%3B%20The%20Bill%20says%20that%20whoever%20commits%20snatching%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20three%20years%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20a%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20the%20word%20terrorism%20has%20been%20defined%20under%20the%20BNS%20Bill%20which%20was%20not%20there%20under%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20provision%20111%20of%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20person%20is%20said%20to%20have%20committed%20a%20terrorist%20act%20if%20he%20commits%20any%20act%20in%20India%20or%20any%20foreign%20country%20with%20the%20intention%20to%20threaten%20the%20unity%2C%20integrity%20and%20security%20of%20India%2C%20to%20intimidate%20the%20general%20public%20or%20a%20segment%20thereof%2C%20or%20to%20disturb%20public%20order%20by%20doing%20an%20act....%26quot%3B%20As%20per%20the%20IPC%2C%20the%20offence%20of%20defamation%20carries%20a%20punishment%20of%20simple%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20two%20years%20or%20a%20fine%20or%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20in%20the%20BNS%20Bill%2C%20the%20offence%20of%20defamation%20carries%20a%20simple%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20two%20years%20or%20a%20fine%2C%20or%20both%20or%20with%20community%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20chapter%20on%20sexual%20offences%20against%20women%20and%20children%2C%20the%20BNS%20Bill%20says%20in%20Section%2069%2C%20%26quot%3BWhoever%2C%20by%20deceitful%20means%20or%20making%20by%20promise%20to%20marry%20to%20a%20woman%20without%20any%20intention%20of%20fulfilling%20the%20same%2C%20and%20has%20sexual%20intercourse%20with%20her%2C%20such%20sexual%20intercourse%20not%20amounting%20to%20the%20offence%20of%20rape%2C%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20either%20description%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20ten%20years%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine.%26quot%3B%20It%20explained%20that%20%26quot%3Bdeceitful%20means%26quot%3B%20shall%20include%20the%20false%20promise%20of%20employment%20or%20promotion%2C%20inducement%20or%20marrying%20after%20suppressing%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691974980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2Fcourt-generic_625x300_1527245477936.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-bns-bill-proposes-to-do-away-with-ipc-provisions-on-unnatural-sex-adultery-4294816%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS)%20Bill%20which%20is%20proposed%20to%20replace%20the%20British-era%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20does%20away%20with%20two%20contentious%20provisions%20on%20unnatural%20sex%20and%20adultery%20that%20were%20diluted%20and%20struck%20down%20respectively%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-bns-bill-proposes-to-do-away-with-ipc-provisions-on-unnatural-sex-adultery-4294816%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-bns-bill-proposes-to-do-away-with-ipc-provisions-on-unnatural-sex-adultery-4294816%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-bns-bill-proposes-to-do-away-with-ipc-provisions-on-unnatural-sex-adultery-4294816%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boy%20survives%20100ft%20Grand%20Canyon%20fall%20after%20dodging%20tourist%20photo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691974883000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F16061%2Fproduction%2F_130790209_gettyimages-122316570.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66495043%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20teenager%20suffered%20serious%20injuries%20when%20he%20plunged%20nearly%20100ft%20(30m).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A412%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%