jor-row-with-electoral-manipulation-charge-news-309827%5C%22%3EBJP%20leaders%20made%20scathing%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20spared%20neither%20Das%20nor%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20fine%20to%20differ%20with%20the%20BJP%20on%20matters%20of%20policy%20but%20this%20is%20taking%20it%20too%20far%E2%80%A6how%20can%20someone%20in%20the%20name%20of%20half-baked%20research%20discredit%20India%E2%80%99s%20vibrant%20poll%20process%3F%20How%20can%20any%20University%20allow%20it%3F%20Answers%20needed-%20this%20is%20not%20good%20enough%20a%20response.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmit%20Malviya%2C%20the%20convenor%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20IT%20cell%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20research%20paper%20by%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20Sabyasachi%20Das%20presents%20several%20datasets%20and%20dozens%20of%20charts%20as%20%E2%80%98evidence%E2%80%99%20of%20what%20he%20calls%20%E2%80%98significant%20irregularities%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98electoral%20fraud%E2%80%99.%20These%20are%20big%20claims.%20Does%20the%20evidence%20stack%20up%3F%20The%20answer%20is%20No%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20abstract%20of%20Das%E2%80%99s%20study%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20paper%20contributes%20to%20the%20discussion%20by%20documenting%20irregular%20patterns%20in%20the%202019%20general%20election%20in%20India%20and%20identifying%20whether%20they%20are%20due%20to%20electoral%20manipulation%20or%20precise%20control%2C%20i.e.%2C%20%5Bthe%5D%20incumbent%20party%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20precisely%20predict%20and%20affect%20win%20margins%20through%20campaigning.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20compile%20several%20new%20datasets%20and%20present%20evidence%20that%20is%20consistent%20with%20electoral%20manipulation%20in%20closely%20contested%20constituencies%20and%20is%20less%20supportive%20of%20the%20precise%20control%20hypothesis.%20The%20manipulation%20appears%20to%20take%20the%20form%20of%20targeted%20electoral%20discrimination%20against%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20minority%20group%20%E2%80%93%20Muslims%2C%20partly%20facilitated%20by%20weak%20monitoring%20by%20election%20observers.%20The%20results%20present%20a%20worrying%20development%20for%20the%20future%20of%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-edict.in%2Fpost%2Fdebate-and-attacks-surround-sabyasachi-das-working-paper-on-democratic-backsliding%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estudent%20newspaper%2C%20The%20Edict%20captured%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20debate%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20underlining%20that%20the%20Economics%20department%20issued%20no%20statement%20and%20the%20stand%20of%20its%20faculty%20on%20Das%E2%80%99s%20conclusions%20is%20not%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESabyasachi%20Das%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ashoka.edu.in%2Fprofile%2Fsabyasachi-das%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECV%20on%20the%20Ashoka%20website%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20that%20he%20has%20received%20his%20Ph.D.%20in%20Economics%20at%20Yale%20University%20in%202015.%20Prior%20to%20joining%20Ashoka%20University%20he%20was%20a%20postdoctoral%20fellow%20at%20the%20prestigious%20Indian%20Statistical%20Institute%2C%20Delhi.%20His%20fields%20of%20specialisation%20are%20political%20economy%2C%20public%20economics%2C%20and%20applied%20microeconomics.%20For%20his%20research%2C%20he%20is%20primarily%20interested%20in%20exploring%20group%20inequalities%20that%20emerge%20from%20various%20democratic%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20his%20CV%2C%20%E2%80%9Che%20has%20studied%20gender%20and%20caste%20issues%20in%20village%20elections%20and%20meetings%20in%20India%2C%20and%20explored%20governance%20consequences%20of%20political%20alignment%20between%20state%20and%20local%20governments%20by%20looking%20at%20appointments%20of%20bureaucrats.%20In%20other%20work%2C%20he%20is%20exploring%20broad%20electoral%20systems%2C%20such%20plurality%20rule%20and%20proportional%20representation%2C%20and%20comparing%20them%20across%20countries%20to%20determine%20their%20effect%20on%20representation%20of%20minorities%20in%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691955401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14005619%2Fcollage.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fauthor-of-paper-on-possible-manipulation-in-2019-polls-quits-ashoka-university%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sabyasachi%20Das%E2%80%99s%20paper%20was%20attacked%20by%20BJP%20leaders%20and%20the%20university%20quickly%20distanced%20itself%20from%20his%20study%2C%20prompting%20accusations%20of%20'democratic%20backsliding%20in%20the%20academia'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fauthor-of-paper-on-possible-manipulation-in-2019-polls-quits-ashoka-university%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20North%20Florida%20congressional%20district%20that%20was%20held%20by%20a%20Black%20Democrat%20before%20it%20was%20dismantled%20by%20Ron%20DeSantis%20could%20be%20restored%20in%202024%20under%20a%20new%20agreement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Al%20Lawson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d925e51f51cc00196887e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThen-House%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi%20of%20California%2C%20left%2C%20poses%20during%20a%20ceremonial%20swearing-in%20with%20then-Rep.%20Al%20Lawson%20of%20Florida%2C%20right%2C%20on%20Capitol%20Hill.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAlex%20Brandon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAn%20agreement%20could%20potentially%20restore%20a%20North%20Florida%20House%20dismantled%20by%20DeSantis%2C%20per%20Politico.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20district%20in%20question%20was%20represented%20by%20Democrat%20Al%20Lawson%2C%20a%20veteran%20Black%20lawmaker.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20agreement%20wouldn't%20end%20the%20litigation%20over%20DeSantis'%20map%2C%20but%20would%20limit%20the%20scope%20of%20arguments%20against%20the%20lines.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20Republican-controlled%20Florida%20legislature%20pushed%20for%20a%20congressional%20map%20that%20would%20gave%20their%20party%20a%20sizable%20edge%20in%20the%202022%20midterms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%2C%20who's%20currently%20running%20for%20the%202024%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination%2C%20wasn't%20satisfied%2C%20submitting%20a%20map%20that%20dismantled%20the%20plurality-Black%20congressional%20district%20of%20then-Democratic%20Rep.%20Al%20Lawson.%20The%20move%20created%20surrounding%20districts%20that%20were%20significantly%20more%20Republican.%20After%20the%20Florida%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F2022-election%2Fflorida-supreme-court-leaves-desantis-congressional-map-place-midterms-rcna31689%5C%22%3Eleft%20DeSantis'%20map%20in%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%202022%20midterms%2C%20the%20GOP%20picked%20up%20four%20House%20seats%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20commanding%2020-8%20statewide%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20an%20ongoing%20legal%20challenge%20to%20the%20state's%20congressional%20maps%20has%20produced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1R2TuSaMYmYz9VNxAHwmWtoo685DVAMRa%2Fview%3Fpli%3D1%5C%22%3Ean%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20restore%20Lawson's%20North%20Florida%20district%20for%20the%202024%20election%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F12%2Fflorida-house-seat-al-lawson-00110962%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Politico%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20agreement%20between%20Florida%20and%20the%20groups%20challenging%20the%20DeSantis-drawn%20congressional%20map%20would%20not%20halt%20litigation%20over%20the%20boundaries%2C%20but%20it%20would%20narrow%20the%20ongoing%20suit%20to%20Lawson's%20district.%20Under%20the%20agreement%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20would%20have%20to%20end%20their%20challenges%20to%20districts%20in%20the%20Orlando%20and%20Tampa%20Bay%20areas%2C%20respectively%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20lawsuit%20involving%20the%20congressional%20maps%20is%20currently%20in%20federal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlivia%20Mendoza%2C%20the%20director%20of%20litigation%20and%20policy%20for%20the%20National%20Redistricting%20Foundation%2C%20praised%20the%20tentative%20agreement%20as%20one%20that%20would%20restore%20an%20element%20of%20fairness%20back%20to%20the%20congressional%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20promising%20step%20forward%20for%20Black%20voters%20whose%20voting%20power%20was%20disgracefully%20targeted%20by%20Gov.%20DeSantis%20in%20his%20quest%20for%20artificial%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Politico.%20%26quot%3BFloridians%20deserve%20fair%20maps%20%E2%80%94%20and%20success%20in%20this%20case%20will%20deliver%20a%20major%20step%20in%20that%20direction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorida%20Republican%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Cord%20Byrd%2C%20a%20defendant%20in%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20told%20Politico%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20comment%20on%20pending%20litigation%20but%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20stipulation%20speaks%20for%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20contingent%20of%20groups%20including%20Black%20Voters%20Matter%2C%20Equal%20Ground%2C%20Florida%20Rising%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flwvfl.org%2Fstate-of-florida-admits-diminishment-of-black-voting-power-in-redistricting-case-agrees-to-path-for-new-remedial-map-for-2024%2F%5C%22%3ELeague%20of%20Women%20Voters%20of%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%20sued%20the%20state%20over%20the%20congressional%20maps%20one%20day%20after%20DeSantis%20signed%20them%20into%20law.%20They%20alleged%20he%20had%20used%20the%20bully%20pulpit%20of%20his%20office%20to%20push%20legislative%20Republicans%20into%20accepting%20his%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Csection%20data-content-section%3D%5C%225%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EA%20trial%20was%20set%20to%20be%20held%20late%20in%20August%2C%20but%20attorneys%20for%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20along%20with%20the%20DeSantis%20administration%20and%20the%20Florida%20legislature%2C%20crafted%20a%20plan%20to%20limit%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EThe%20trial%20is%20now%20set%20to%20focus%20on%20whether%20the%20redistricting%20law%20approved%20by%20Florida%20votes%20violates%20the%20equal%20protection%20clause.%20It%20will%20not%20include%20arguments%20over%20whether%20or%20not%20several%20districts%20were%20constructed%20to%20boost%20Republicans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EUnder%20the%20Fair%20Districts%20provision%20approved%20by%20voters%2C%20districts%20can't%20be%20formulated%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bdiminish%26quot%3B%20the%20opportunity%20for%20minority%20voters%20to%20select%20a%20candidate%20of%20their%20choice.%20But%20when%20DeSantis%20submitted%20his%20own%20map%2C%20he%20tore%20apart%20Lawson's%205th%20Congressional%20District%2C%20which%20ran%20from%20areas%20west%20of%20Tallahassee%20to%20Jacksonville.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EDeSantis%20said%20Lawson's%20district%20was%20unconstitutional%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20was%20an%20illegal%20racial%20gerrymander.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EA%20recent%20decision%20from%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20where%20the%20conservative-dominated%20body%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsupreme-court-redistricting-race-voting-rights-alabama-af0d789ec7498625d344c0a4327367fe%5C%22%3Eruled%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%20weakening%20protections%20of%20the%20Voting%20Rights%20Act%20may%20have%20given%20the%20plaintiffs%20a%20major%20boost%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20challenge%20the%20DeSantis-drawn%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20agreement%20that%20was%20filed%20late%20last%20week%2C%20attorneys%20for%20the%20governor%20and%20the%20legislature%20stated%20that%20%26quot%3Bnone%20of%20the%20enacted%20districts%20in%20North%20Florida%20are%20districts%20in%20which%20Black%20voters%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20elect%20their%20preferred%20candidates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawson%2C%20who%20ran%20for%20reelection%20in%202022%20and%20lost%20to%20Neal%20Dunn%20in%20the%20heavily%202nd%20Republican%20district%2C%20told%20Politico%20on%20Saturday%20he%20would%20think%20about%20running%20for%20Congress%20again%20should%20his%20old%20district%20be%20restored%20to%20a%20configuration%20similar%20to%20the%20district%20that%20he%20represented%20before%20last%20year's%20midterms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdesantis-democratic-congressional-district-restored-agreement-black-voters-gop-lawson-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691955356000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d926141f51cc00196887fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdesantis-democratic-congressional-district-restored-agreement-black-voters-gop-lawson-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Democratic%20Rep.%20Al%20Lawson%20was%20booted%20from%20office%20after%20he%20ran%20in%20a%20GOP-heavy%20district%20created%20by%20DeSantis.%20He%20may%20end%20up%20back%20in%20Congress%20next%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdesantis-democratic-congressional-district-restored-agreement-black-voters-gop-lawson-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%