0the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIssuing%20the%20warning%20on%20July%2018%2C%20the%20NMC%20noted%20the%20doctor%20has%20contributed%20immensely%20to%20the%20field%20of%20reproductive%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20spite%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20act%20in%20question%20was%20done%20in%20good%20faith%20to%20benefit%20the%20poor%20patients%20without%20accruing%20any%20personal%20gain%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20denied%20that%20prevailing%20guidelines%20were%20violated.%20So%2C%20the%20doctor%20is%20warned%20to%20be%20more%20careful%20in%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20order%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20had%20appealed%20to%20the%20National%20Medical%20Commission%20after%20the%20Delhi%20Medical%20Council%20(DMC)%20in%20September%20last%20year%20ordered%20the%20suspension%20of%20her%20license%20for%20one%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20complaint%20received%20by%20the%20DMC%20in%202017%2C%2030%20eggs%20were%20retrieved%20from%20the%20patient%20on%20August%2012%20of%20that%20year%20for%20an%20IVF%20procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2C%2014%20were%20taken%20by%20the%20doctor%20from%20the%20embryologist%20and%20provided%20those%20to%20two%20patients%20without%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20woman%2C%20said%20Dr%20Girish%20Tyagi%2C%20the%20secretary%20of%20DMC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20disciplinary%20committee%20of%20the%20DMC%20investigated%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20the%20DMC%20observed%20that%20%26quot%3Bsharing%20a%20patient's%20eggs%2Foocytes%20is%20not%20only%20illegal%2C%20as%20sharing%2Fdonation%20of%20such%20nature%20is%20prohibited%20as%20per%20the%20ICMR%20guidelines%2C%20but%20also%20unethical%2C%20moreover%2C%20when%20no%20written%20consent%20of%20the%20donor%20as%20well%20as%20recipient%20as%20per%20the%20guidelines%20have%20been%20made%20available%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Medical%20Council.%26quot%3B%20The%20AIIMS%20in%20its%20internal%20enquiry%20report%20dated%20August%2030%2C%202017%2C%20also%20highlighted%20the%20lapses%20committed%20by%20the%20doctor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20complained%20to%20the%20DMC%20that%20the%20doctor%20was%20originally%20appointed%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Reproductive%20Biology%20and%20then%20transferred%20to%20the%20gynaecology%20department%20against%20the%20recruitment%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20document%2C%20the%20doctor%20claimed%20before%20the%20DMC%20that%20since%20both%20her%20patients%20had%20multiple%20failed%20IVF%20cycles%20in%20the%20past%2C%20she%20shared%20the%20eggs%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20and%20helped%20the%20recipients%20without%20comprising%20with%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20patient%20from%20whom%20the%20eggs%20were%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20confirming%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20disciplinary%20Committee%2C%20the%20DMC%20observed%20that%20in%20light%20of%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20lapse%20committed%20by%20the%20doctor%2C%20the%20punishment%20of%20warning%20awarded%20by%20the%20disciplinary%20committee%20%26quot%3Bwill%20not%20serve%20the%20interest%20of%20justice%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHence%2C%20the%20council%20directs%20that%20punishment%20awarded%20be%20enhanced%20and%20the%20name%20of%20the%20doctor%20be%20removed%20from%20State%20Medical%20Register%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Medical%20Council%20for%20a%20period%20of%2030%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DMC%20stated%20in%20its%20September%2019%2C%202022%2C%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20then%20appealed%20to%20the%20NMC%20on%20October%203%20seeking%20the%20quashing%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Medical%20Council%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20committee%20under%20the%20DMC%20failed%20to%20differentiate%20the%20bona%20fide%20case%20of%20egg%20sharing%20granted%20in%20ICMR%20guidelines%20followed%20at%20that%20time%20with%20allegations%20of%20clandestine%20stealing%20of%20eggs%20made%20in%20the%20anonymous%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20complex%20procedure%20of%20egg%20retrieval%2C%20fertilisation%20and%20sharing%20was%20done%20by%20the%20entire%20IVF%20team%20in%20consultation%20with%20all%20stakeholders%2C%20including%20the%20treating%20physician%20and%20was%20recorded%20in%20the%20lab%20documents%20in%20a%20transparent%20manner%20known%20to%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20doctor%20had%20said%20in%20her%20appeal%20to%20the%20NMC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ethics%20and%20Medical%20Registration%20Board%20of%20the%20National%20Medical%20Council%20held%20a%20meeting%20on%20October%2018%2C%20last%20year%2C%20and%20accepted%20the%20appeal%20while%20granting%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20DMC%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20an%20enquiry%20by%20the%20board%20and%20a%20hearing%20on%20May%2024%2C%20the%20NMC%20let%20off%20the%20doctor%20with%20a%20warning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691950560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-12%2Ff97731ac_aiims-delhi-generic_625x300_01_December_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faiims-doctor-shares-patients-eggs-without-consent-let-off-with-warning-4294902%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20doctor%20of%20the%20AIIMS-Delhi's%20gynaecology%20department%20who%20provided%20some%20eggs%20from%20a%20patient%20undergoing%20IVF%20treatment%20to%20two%20women%20without%20her%20consent%20in%20violation%20of%20ICMR's%20guidelines%20has%20been%20let%20off%20with%20a%20warning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faiims-doctor-shares-patients-eggs-without-consent-let-off-with-warning-4294902%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faiims-doctor-shares-patients-eggs-without-consent-le