3ENow%2C%20more%20than%20100%20years%20after%20the%20first%20Dreadnought%2C%20another%20is%20in%20the%20works.%20This%20one%2C%20the%20first%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fdreadnought-class-nuclear-powered-ballistic-missile-submarines%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20class%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic-missile%20submarines%2C%20will%20again%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20warship%20for%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAt-sea%20deterrent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22British%20Royal%20Navy%20submarine%20HMS%20Dreadnought%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b171ec14ba0019f33de1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Royal%20Navy%20submarine%20HMS%20Dreadnought%20in%20April%201963.%3Cp%3ESSPL%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBritain's%20new%20class%20of%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic-missile%20submarines%2C%20designated%20as%20SSBNs%2C%20will%20fill%20a%20looming%20gap%20in%20the%20country's%20nuclear%20deterrent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%20other%20nuclear-armed%20countries%20employ%20a%20triad%20of%20delivery%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20ground-launched%2C%20air-launched%2C%20and%20sea-launched%20%E2%80%94%20to%20ensure%20their%20nuclear%20capability%20will%20survive%20an%20attack%20and%20thus%20guarantee%20a%20credible%20nuclear%20deterrent%2C%20Britain%20has%20relied%20solely%20on%20submarine-launched%20ballistic%20missiles%20since%201998%2C%20when%20it%20retired%20its%20air-dropped%20nuclear%20gravity%20bombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Royal%20Navy%20has%20had%20at%20least%20one%20SSBN%20on%20patrol%20as%20part%20of%20Operation%20Relentless%2C%20Britain's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fnews-and-latest-activity%2Foperations%2Fglobal%2Fcontinuous-at-sea-deterrent%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinuous%20at%20sea%20deterrent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%201969%2C%20making%20it%20the%20country's%20longest%20ongoing%20military%20operation.%20The%20current%20British%20SSBN%20force%20is%20made%20up%20of%20four%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fthe-equipment%2Fsubmarines%2Fballistic-submarines%2Fvanguard-class%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanguard-class%3C%2Fa%3E%20subs%2C%20which%20were%20built%20between%201986%20and%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strain%20of%20decades%20of%20near-constant%20deployments%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20Vanguards.%20Originally%20meant%20to%20serve%20for%2025%20years%2C%20the%20subs%20have%20had%20their%20service%20lives%20extended%20three%20times.%20Their%20overall%20lifespan%20is%20now%20expected%20to%20be%2037%20to%2038%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vanguard-class%20submarine%20HMS%20Victorious%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b6f8ec14ba0019f347b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221206%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVanguard-class%20submarine%20HMS%20Victorious%20near%20Faslane%20in%20April%202013.%3Cp%3EUK%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20the%20British%20Parliament%20approved%20a%20plan%20for%20four%20new%20SSBNs%20to%20replace%20the%20Vanguards.%20After%20years%20of%20design%20work%2C%20construction%20on%20the%20first%20boat%2C%20HMS%20Dreadnought%2C%20began%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20successful%20and%20efficient%20construction%20and%20delivery%20of%20the%20new%20class%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20created%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Forganisations%2Fsubmarine-delivery-agency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubmarine%20Delivery%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017%20to%20serve%20as%20an%20executive%20agency%20responsible%20for%20procurement%2C%20in-service%20support%2C%20and%20decommissioning%20of%20all%20Royal%20Navy%20nuclear%20submarines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20the%20two%20companies%20contracted%20to%20build%20the%20Dreadnought%2C%20BAE%20Systems%20and%20Rolls%20Royce%2C%20formed%20the%20%26quot%3BDreadnought%20Alliance%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20commercial%20arrangement%20that%20ensures%20constant%20communication%20and%20collaboration%20between%20the%20companies%2C%20including%20on%20things%20like%20a%20common%20cost%20model%2C%20mutually%20agreed%20scheduling%20and%20breakdown%20of%20work%2C%20and%20reporting%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Dreadnought%20class%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22931%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22British%20Royal%20Navy%20ballistic-missile%20submarine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b6f7ec14ba0019f347ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22638%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20rendering%20from%202016%20of%20the%20ballistic-missile%20sub%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Vanguard%20class.%3Cp%3EBritish%20Royal%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20about%20500%20feet%20long%20and%20with%20a%20displacement%20of%2017%2C200%20tons%2C%20the%20Dreadnoughts%20will%20be%20the%20largest%20submarines%20ever%20built%20by%20the%20UK.%20Each%20boat%20will%20have%20a%20lifespan%20of%20at%20least%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20Dreadnought%20will%20be%20powered%20by%20the%20PWR3%2C%20a%20new%20nuclear%20reactor%20built%20by%20Rolls-Royce.%20They%20will%20also%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globecomposite.com%2Fblog%2Fx-factor-columbia-class-submarine-design%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX-form%20rudders%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20new%20turbo-electric%20drive%20that%20powers%20an%20electric%20motor%20that%20drives%20an%20improved%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fthe-war-zone%2F31708%2Fveteran-sonarman-explains-why-pump-jets-are-superior-to-props-on-modern-submarines%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epump-jet%20propulsor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20likely%20making%20them%20quieter%20than%20their%20Vanguard-class%20predecessors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20quieting%20features%20of%20their%20propulsion%20systems%2C%20the%20Dreadnoughts%20will%20have%20an%20angular%20design%20meant%20to%20deflect%20active%20sonar%20waves%2C%20making%20them%20stealthier.%20Concept%20imagery%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fnaval-news%2F2021%2F11%2Ffirst-submarine-to-use-new-stealth-technology%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindicates%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Dreadnoughts%20will%20also%20be%20coated%20with%20anechoic%20tiles%2C%20which%20are%20designed%20to%20absorb%20incoming%20active%20sonar%20waves%20and%20reduce%20noise%20from%20the%20sub%20that%20could%20be%20picked%20up%20by%20passive%20sonar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Royal%20Navy%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fnews-and-latest-activity%2Fnews%2F2023%2Fjuly%2F13%2F20230713-scope-for-success-as-historic-glasgow-firm-wins-169m-contract-for-dreadnought-periscopes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplans%20to%20equip%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20Dreadnought%20subs%20with%20optronic%20masts%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-us-british-navy-submarines-have-new-kind-of-periscope-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-tech%20replacement%20for%20the%20traditional%20periscope%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20already%20in%20use%20on%20its%20Astute-class%20submarines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221653%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22trident%20ii%202%20icbm%20missile%20submarine%20launch%20GettyImages%2051102409%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a9db93302957d25008b46ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221240%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Trident%20II%20D-5%20missile%20is%20launched%20from%20a%20US%20Navy%20Ohio-class%20sub%20during%20a%20test.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Dreadnoughts%20will%20have%20four%2021-inch%20torpedo%20tubes%20and%20carry%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seaforces.org%2Fwpnsys%2FSUBMARINE%2FSpearfish-torpedo.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpearfish%20heavyweight%20torpedoes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20main%20armament%2C%20however%2C%20will%20be%2012%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Ftrident-ii-d5-fleet-ballistic-missile%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrident%20II%20D5%3C%2Fa%3E%20ballistic%20missiles%20%E2%80%94%20four%20fewer%20than%20on%20the%20Vanguard-class%20subs%20%E2%80%94%20carrying%20Mk4%2FA%20%26quot%3BHolbrook%26quot%3B%20nuclear%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20missiles%20will%20be%20stored%20and%20launched%20from%20the%20Common%20Missile%20Compartment.%20The%20CMC%20is%20a%20joint%20US-UK%20defense%20project%20begun%20in%202008%20to%20create%20a%20common%20launch%20system%20for%20all%20future%20American%20and%20British%20SSBNs.%20Each%20CMC%20contains%20four%20missile%20silos.%20Dreadnoughts%20will%20be%20equipped%20with%20three%20CMCs%2C%20while%20the%20US%20Navy's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnavy-may-keep-ohio-missile-subs-longer-over-columbia-cost-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColumbia-class%20boats%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20have%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20CMC%20project%2C%20the%20UK%20is%20also%20involved%20in%20the%20US%20Navy's%20Trident%20II%20D5%20service-life%20extension%20program%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20stretch%20the%20missile's%20service%20life%20as%20far%20as%20the%20early%202060s.%20The%20British%20government%20previously%20indicated%20that%20its%20Tridents%20will%20need%20to%20be%20replaced%20in%20the%202040s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20future%20fleet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Royal%20Navy%20submarine%20HMS%20Astute%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b6f8ec14ba0019f347ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERoyal%20Navy%20attack%20sub%20HMS%20Astute%20after%20its%20launch%20at%20a%20shipyard%20in%20Barrow-in-Furness%20in%20June%202007.%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Furlong%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20Dreadnought-class%20subs%20will%20be%20built%3A%20Dreadnought%2C%20Valiant%2C%20Warspite%2C%20and%20King%20George%20VI.%20Construction%20of%20Valiant%20started%20in%202019%20and%20work%20on%20Warspite%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fnews-and-latest-activity%2Fnews%2F2023%2Ffebruary%2F09%2F20230209-work-starts-on-third-new-nuclear-deterrence-submarine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202022%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20announced%20that%20Dreadnought%20had%20entered%20Delivery%20Phase%203%2C%20during%20which%20the%20sub%20will%20eventually%20leave%20the%20BAE%20shipyard%20in%20Barrow-in-Furness%20for%20sea%20trials%2C%20yielding%20lessons%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearchbriefings.files.parliament.uk%2Fdocuments%2FCBP-8010%2FCBP-8010.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20be%20applied%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20construction%20of%20other%20Dreadnought-class%20subs.%20The%20Royal%20Navy%20plans%20to%20commission%20HMS%20Dreadnought%20sometime%20in%20the%20early%202030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20being%20the%20largest%20British%20subs%20ever%2C%20the%20Dreadnought%20class%20will%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20defense%20projects%20in%20British%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20the%20four%20subs%20is%20expected%20to%20cost%20a%20little%20over%20%2439.5%20billion%2C%20a%20total%20that%20includes%20inflation%20over%20the%2035-year%20life%20of%20the%20program.%20The%20British%20government%20has%20also%20set%20up%20a%20contingency%20fund%20of%20about%20%2412.75%20billion%2C%20money%20that%20can%20be%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearchbriefings.files.parliament.uk%2Fdocuments%2FCBP-8010%2FCBP-8010.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ere-profiled%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20to%20keep%20the%20program%20on%20track.%20The%20MoD%20has%20already%20accessed%20about%2020%25%20of%20the%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20British%20lawmakers%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommittees.parliament.uk%2Fpublications%2F22125%2Fdocuments%2F164255%2Fdefault%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpressed%20concern%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20would%20view%20the%20contingency%20fund%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20blank%20cheque%2C%20freeing%20it%20from%20the%20need%20to%20control%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said%20in%20its%202022%20update%20to%20Parliament%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fpublications%2Fthe-united-kingdoms-future-nuclear-deterrent-the-2022-update-to-parliament%2Fthe-united-kingdoms-future-nuclear-deterrent-the-2022-update-to-parliament%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20the%20program%20was%20still%20on%20schedule%20and%20within%20its%20cost%20estimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbritish-us-navies-working-together-to-build-new-dreadnought-submarine-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691930281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b790ec14ba0019f348